snippet.textDisplay: Ohh jeez Hard Kaur is so generic even for someone who rarely listens to rap. "Ohh look I am so focused...I have been through shit...I believe in myself". Write about something else for a change. And the vocal delivery is so uninspired, the rap is totally misplaced and ruins the song in my opinion. Bhanvari Devi should have sang the entire song. Her voice is powerful and high pitched. If you listen to classic hard rock and heavy metal bands, you know that high pitched powerful vocals, heavy low pitched guitar & bass riffs and drums go really well together.

snippet.textDisplay: I dont get the rap haters - how would it be fusion if only Bhanvari Devi sang ?  Ram Sampath is a genius in my opinion to successfully fuse them.  And in the process, keep the music quality such that each instrument is bold yet we can hear it and the vocals at the same time.   As for the photography, its good but take some lessons from the folks at Coke Studios Pakistan.  They have the same polycarbonate sound shields, but manage to work around it.
